at about 10 am sunday on a mud bar about halfway betwen girdwood 
and portage along the seward highway south of anchorage 
dozens of people jammed the roadside to watch the silverwhite 
whales gently flopping on the mud steam rising from their 
blowholes the whales ranged in size from about 6feetlong to 
16feetlong 
