mudflats and swirling currents to spend more than an hour with the 
whales pouring water on them and wrapping them in wet tarps and 
blankets until they could swim free 
they were all alive they looked all wrinkly when we first got 
there and when we left they werent wrinkly any more diehl said 
a helicopter ferried veterinarian tex cody and national oceanic 
and atmospheric administration biologists to the stranded animals 
