editors note they are the clown cops of cincinnati ohio a 
dynamic duo that tries to defuse domestic disturbances with a bit 
of humor an idea that came from a psychologist in upstate new 
york like a poet once said laughter is their shield most of the 
time it works they say but not always 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
when they got the call to investigate a domestic disturbance 
the two cops in cincinnati ohio went into their act 
they pulled down their hats to make their ears protrude 
loosened their ties buttoned their shirts askew and rapped on the 
door playfully with a shave and a haircut beat 
is that your car down there with the lights on the officers 
deadpanned as an angry man opened the door 
the man seeing the oddball cops forgot he was angry and broke 
into a smile 
its a trick the cincinnati police department learned from a 
psychologist in troy ny 
police arriving at the scene of a domestic dispute for 
instance should try performing a bugs bunny impression or try 
raiding the refrigerator before unholstering their nightsticks 
says robert a baron chairman of the psychology department at 
rensselaer polytechnic institute in troy welltimed clowning 
often deters violence more effectively than the threat of force 
cincinnati police officials concede that they were skeptical 
when they first heard baron explain his idea on a local talk show 
but since they began trying it in 1983 theyre finding it works 
our bottomline goal is to resolve conflict with the least 
amount of force says michael gardner a cincinatti police 
officer who teaches the humor technique to new recruits just 
having the police show up doesnt necessarily get attention 
baron was teaching at purdue university in lafayette ind in 
the early 1970s when he first came up with the idea of using humor 
to defuse potentially violent situations 
the basic idea of the research centered on incompatible 
responses he says if someone is angry you do something that 
will make them feel good youll reduce their anger and the things 
that follow it like aggression 
the basic rule of thumb is that when people are experiencing 
strong emotions their logical thinking decreases the research 
tries to counter this we try to pull people toward a calmer 
state 
gardner says barons ideas work best in domestic disputes 
the more emotionally upset someone is the more effective it 
is he says in a family fight a person can be so locked into 
whats going on they can have blinders on 
baron explains that once you get people off the track their 
anger decreases but he concedes that this technique may defuse a 
volatile situation only temporarily 
the idea is to get in quickly and stop the process he says 
its done early in the process when anger is just beginning 
its not powerful late in the process then you might want to 
withdraw 
gardner was the first officer in cincinnati to try clowning but 
he soon persuaded his partner to join him he says they developed 
several acts 
wed often knock with a shave and a haircut beat to it 
says gardner a 15year veteran of the force 
once inside if the parties insisted on fighting gardner and 
his partner would start rearranging the furniture in the room 
saying they needed space to loosen up for the fight 
gardner says he was once caught off guard by his partner who 
gave a firstrate performance and stopped a violent family 
fight 
he threw his hat down during a domestic dispute and said he 
didnt have to take this anymore gardner says eventually this 
guy we had been telling to leave told my partner its no big 
deal ill go take a walk 
gardner says teaching the technique to new recruits at the 
police academy is not always an easy job because they have 
preconceived ideas of what a police officer is and have a rough 
em up attitude he says 
on the other hand he says experienced officers think its 
the best training theyve ever had 
gardner took a leave of absence a year ago to travel around the 
country sharing what he knew with other police departments 
he says he knows of no other police departments using the 
technique but many are becoming interested 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP881024-0205 </DOCNO>
