<TEXT>
nwa inc reported that strong passenger 
traffic helped to boost its thirdquarter profit 332 percent from 
a year earlier and to lift quarterly earnings over 100 million for 
the first time 
the parent of northwest airlines said monday that its net income 
in the three months ended sept 30 jumped to 1163 million or 
398 a share from 873 million or 289 a share a year earlier 
thirdquarter revenue rose to 161 billion from 144 billion 
these results are the highest quarterly profits in our 62year 
history and mark the first time net earnings for a quarter exceeded 
100 million said nwa chairman steven g rothmeier 
our thirdquarter results were characterized by strong 
passenger traffic and improved yield the measurement of revenue 
per passenger mile rothmeier said in a statement 
a passenger mile represents one paying passenger flown one mile 
and is used to determine an airlines capacity 
northwest had a 56 percent increase in passenger traffic over 
the third quarter of 1987 rothmeier said 
in the first nine months of the year nwa earned 1011 million 
or 347 a share compared with 103 million or 359 a share in 
the yearearlier period the thirdquarter profit offset a net loss 
in the first half of the year 
