copper futures prices took their sharpest dive in nearly four 
months monday on new yorks commodity exchange as traders took 
profits after bidding up prices to an alltime high last week 
on other markets precious metals futures declined as energy 
prices tumbled pork bellies rallied strongly livestock futures 
were mixed grains and soybeans were mostly lower and stockindex 
futures retreated 
the comex spot copper price plunged 385 cents to 1414 a pound 
while the contract for delivery in december fell 3 cents to 
13325 the steepest drop in the copper market since july 1 
analysts said copper prices were due for a correction after 
climbing by 60 percent since early august to a record 1465 a 
pound during fridays trading the spot price settled friday below 
the record level reached during the day 
mondays stronger dollar and weaker oil prices provided a 
bearish backdrop for the entire metals complex 
but the strongest sell signal for copper traders appeared to be 
the london metal exchanges report of a 7900metricton decline 
last week in its warehouse stocks of the metal the market had been 
