<TEXT>
kraft inc said monday it would give advance 
notice if it decided to proceed with any part of its 136 billion 
defensive restructuring without the approval of its directors and 
shareholders 
krafts statement in federal court in chicago was a victory for 
the company pursuing kraft philip morris cos inc which had 
sought a temporary restraining order asking for three days notice 
of any restructuring moves 
kraft is seeking to boost its debt more than tenfold in order to 
make a huge payout to its shareholders that would convince them not 
to go along with a takeover offer of more than 11 billion from 
philip morris 
us district judge james b moran rejected philip morriss 
request for a temporary restraining order saying it was unneeded 
because of krafts agreement to give advance notice to the court 
philip morris chairman and chief executive hamish maxwell 
criticized the restructuring as lacking in details and being 
dependent upon the breakup of kraft 
the restructuring plan will require burdening what is left 
of kraft with an enormous debt mortgaging its future maxwell 
said 
a spokesperson for kraft said later monday that disparaging 
remarks made by philip morris regarding the recapitalization plan 
are totally consistent with philip morriss pressure tactics to 
buy kraft on the cheap 
some experts agreed with philip morriss criticism of the kraft 
moves arguing that krafts plan fails the litmus test for a 
successful restructuring the company is not mismanaged and its 
assets are not undervalued thereby limiting managements ability 
to squeeze out the extra dollars needed to pay down billions in 
fresh debt 
they cant service debt at that level said ronald morrow 
an analyst at smith barney harris upham amp co referring to 
interest and principal payments that will have to be made on what 
kraft estimates will add up to more than 124 billion in debt 
they cant earn enough from their businesses to cover the 
leverage he said monday adding in jest that kraft is going to 
have to sell off all the assets 
on sunday kraft management rejected as inadequate philip 
morriss 90ashare cash offer and unveiled its own restructuring 
plan valued at 110 a share 
glenview illbased kraft maker of velveeta cheese and 
sealtest ice creams said some noncore businesses would be sold to 
raise cash but the plan also hinges on bank borrowings and the 
issuance of junk bonds in order to pay shareholders 84 a share in 
cash shareholders also would receive securities and retain an 
interest in their common shares 
in heavy trading on the new york stock exchange kraft soared 
10 a share to close at 102 
under these circumstances its either buy the company or 
get had said stephen carnes a managing director at 
minneapolisbased piper jaffray amp hopwood 
but observers also conceded the restructuring might just be a 
strategy designed to goad philip morris into sweetening its offer 
indeed kraft said in a statement that it advised philip morris 
that we were not foreclosing negotiations and that if they were to 
offer a price that reflects the full value of kraft we would 
negotiate 
if that strategy proves successful it would be a plus for 
kraft management said edward froelich an analyst at pershing 
amp co if not it wont be the first time a company has gone to 
the cleaners to stay in business under current management he 
said 
a restructuring if implemented would take its toll on the 
company for several years to come its going to take all the 
earnings out of the company and put them all in dividends 
carnes said it doesnt make a lot of business sense 
kraft has been undergoing a transformation for several years in 
an effort to shed its nonfood operations in 1986 the company 
formed premark international inc to spin off its consumer products 
operations with the 18 billion sale of its duracell batteries 
unit this summer to a management group led by the buyout powerhouse 
kohlberg kravis roberts amp co kraft finally returned to its roots 
as a food and food services concern 
theyve really only just become a food company in the last two 
quarters said carnes the restructuring currently on the table 
is the last thing youd do in a normal business environment he 
added 
kraft admitted as much in announcing the restructuring the 
company called the plan a product of current era investment 
policies and financial attitues that favor shortterm financial 
gratification over steady longterm growth and the need to provide 
a sound economy for future generations 
analysts were concerned over which businesses kraft might 
consider selling carnes speculated the companys food ingredients 
business might be on the block kraft sells oils seasonings 
cheese products and other ingredients to food processors and 
foodservice customers 
worse however kraft might opt to sell its frozen foods 
operations as a package partly because the majority of products in 
this category do not carry the kraft name and therefore could be 
easily separated from the company some of the products include 
lenders bagels tombstone pizzas and the budget gourmet 
the whole industry is going into frozen foods said carnes 
lamenting that it would be a real crime if kraft were forced to 
sell one of the trendy businesses 
