investment banker frank g zarb has been 
named chairman and chief executive of the investment firm smith 
barney inc it was announced monday 
zarb replaces george a vonder linden who resigned the 
appointment is effective nov 1 
the appointment was announced jointly by gerald tsai jr 
chairman of primerica corp and sanford i weill chairman of 
commercial credit group inc 
primerica acquired smith barney in june 1987 primerica and 
commercial credit group announced plans in august to merge before 
the end of the year 
zarb is a senior partner at lazard freres amp co where he 
conducts a broad range of investment banking activities including 
international and domestic corporate finance and mergers and 
acquisitions he acts as adviser to the united states congress and 
other governmental agencies 
a former adviser to president gerald r ford zarb joined lazard 
freres in january 1978 after serving in various capacities at 
predecessor firms to shearson lehman hutton inc 
primerica based in greenwich is engaged in financial services 
and specialty retailing 
commercial credit group inc provides consumers with lending and 
savings products as well as credit rated insurance primarily 
through a network of more than 435 branch offices 
